{{Infobox language |name=Phunyot |nativename= |states=[[Laos]] |region= |ethnicity= |speakers=? |date= |ref= |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Lolo–Burmese languages|Lolo–Burmese]] |fam4=[[Loloish languages|Loloish]] |fam5=[[Southern Loloish languages|Southern]] |fam6=[[Bisoid languages|Bisoid]] |iso3=none |glotto=none }}
'''Phunyot''' (''{{IPA|pʰu˨˩ɲɔt˩}}'') is a [[Loloish language]] of northern [[Laos]].
Phunyot is spoken in [[Namo District]], [[Oudomxai province]], including in Namkang village (Kato 2008).
